{
  "texts": [
    "We noticed the following pattern while working with the chatbot interface: the more information is provided to ChatGPT about a concrete story, the more creative it could be while writing character lines.",
    "If AI is asked to generate dialogue from scratch, the replicas will be stereotypical, the characters will speak like robots, and readers will not feel an emotional connection with the story.",
    "It was also noticed that the Chabot can mix different styles of writing, and it leads to an unexpected result the human author must take into consideration.",
    "For example, in a friendly conversation two teenagers are talking as if they were discussing important ethical issues of preserving memories in a university lecture (Table 1, Story 2).",
    "Human writers try to avoid such generalization in their novels by adding distinctive details that fully reveal the issue."
  ]
}